<subSubSection id="E9440A3025DBCB430F1AFE2E99CD98D9" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="description">
<paragraph id="1D7B4E389AD01F1C84BA6A51E83DBC44" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Male.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AB5F07E29FA2BAC619F73AD8FF10D21F" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Figures 
<figureCitation id="C825282BC48E4BFAE73AF3638DB09187" captionStart="Figure 26" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 26. Pampsilota nigeriae: Penis valve (left, lateral aspect)." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.64.10800.figure26" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/118798" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">26</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="BF7C6C9833C813F0BF16FEF31D7209D7" captionStart="Figures 60–65" captionStartId="F16" captionText="Figures 60 - 65. Pampsilota leleupi ♂ (HT), dorsal / lateral. 62 - 63. Pampsilota luederitzensis ♂ (PT), dorsal / lateral. 64 - 65. Pampsilota nigeriae ♂ (HT), dorsal / lateral. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.64.10800.figures60-65" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/118815" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">64-65</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
<caption id="6E030E594A0CB34AC31408D02A756F62" ID-Zenodo-Dep="987877" doi="10.3897/dez.64.10800.figure26" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/118798" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" start="Figure 26" startId="F8">
<paragraph id="40BEA847E3328384E4D2C4129D3F5E0E" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis id="1DD06575C7A9AD642CAC00F1D217B080" bold="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Figure 26.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="6540478F0C461A3F4161347E19F54721" authority="Konow, 1899" authorityName="Liston &amp; Koch" authorityYear="2017" class="Insecta" family="Argidae" genus="Pampsilota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pampsilota nigeriae" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigeriae">
<emphasis id="644F7B76C662A0325968840F87C25025" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Pampsilota nigeriae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: Penis valve (left, lateral aspect).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="6E0196646D21D8EAA99B2932B831362A" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Head black; labrum yellow; antenna light brown with blackish apex and sharply compressed longitudinal carina. Thorax yellow with following black: mesoscutum except for a small median spot between lateral lobes on posterior margin, mesoscutellum and metascutellum. Legs yellow; metatibia and metatarsomeres moderately broadly blackish-ringed apically, tarsomeres 3/4 nearly entirely black. Wings including intercostal area slightly infuscate; substigmal spot weakly developed, stigma bicoloured with dirty whitish base and blackish apical half, costa whitish, subcosta except for apex adjacent to stigma and rest of venation blackish. Abdomen yellow.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1DF64F8796C5354620D9B74130A15D54" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Head slightly narrowed behind eyes. Antenna 1.6
<normalizedToken id="A750B09E38BE8790F4EFE4AEA6C6C1D6" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as maximum head width; flagellum very slightly enlarged towards apex, triangular in cross section, scarcely flattened apically, interior surface with sharply compressed longitudinal carina, other longitudinal carinae weakly compressed. Eyes very slightly converging towards clypeus. Anterior margin of clypeus semi-circularly emarginate over its entire width; supraclypeal area very slightly rounded, protruding up to ventral limit of interantennal carinae, interantennal carinae obtusely ridged, converging below, extending to a little below ventral margin of torulus. Frons, supraclypeal area and clypeus densely punctate, weakly shiny, vertex and gena scattered micropunctate, shiny; pubescence whitish. Mesoscutum moderately densely punctate, shiny; pubescence similar to that on head. Abdomen smooth and shiny. Penis valve: Fig. 
<figureCitation id="EFDC47ACE02ECCF585AAD7E308E216E8" captionStart="Figure 26" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 26. Pampsilota nigeriae: Penis valve (left, lateral aspect)." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.64.10800.figure26" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/118798" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">26</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9CBABF4DCC241513CA03F2B66FAD59EC" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Length: 7.3 mm.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C057967DFE8E6C63BA74787F2C5643F6" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="description">
<paragraph id="AA0DDB052F7E93988E5EA77CAEBAB731" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Female.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="706643CDEAD97A422EBF52FE968033CB" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FB2B0865C493B53C3056FFBA97C1753F" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="type material">
<paragraph id="BBC8D2A4E7C4F4A58640A9728589313E" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Type material.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="18537FBDAD19B8D0C25DB1ED34C9932A" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Holotype: ♂. Labels: &quot;Nigeria, 14.V.2011, 26 km SEE Abuja, N 09°06
<normalizedToken id="87569369AB97149136E61AE45F3F31AE" originalValue="’/E07°45’">'/E07°45'</normalizedToken>
, 400 m, J. Halada leg.&quot;; &quot; DEI-GISHym 21248&quot;; &quot;Holotype, 
<taxonomicName id="EDAE10CD64F0D2D0382A1CCF878ADC57" authority="Konow, 1899" authorityName="Liston &amp; Koch" authorityYear="2017" class="Insecta" family="Argidae" genus="Pampsilota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pampsilota nigeriae" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigeriae">
<emphasis id="08AC15D0CB2D15F37DE5338A93035EC0" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Pampsilota nigeriae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
n. sp. ♂, det.: F. Koch, 2016&quot; [red] (OLML).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C92EDFAEB7DE5EF34948F5D195147841" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="C179E44A22D6BF7C7E8915891020462D" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A0A0426234699E1A8C3D1882B89FE135" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">The new species is named after Nigeria, the country in which the holotype was collected.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="59878994A193C2C5CD678F02C27B6652" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="0144C2B6463093743A292C2215BC4F70" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B2E1F912C950900A6E372EAC87BA1340" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Nigeria (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="F38948032683F6E31078FFB40BD14ED1" captionStart="Figure 37" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 37. Distribution map for Pampsilota leleupi, Pampsilota luederitzensis, Pampsilota nigeriae, Pampsilota tsavoensis, and Pampsilota zebra." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.64.10800.figure37" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/118807" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">37</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1291687C31D721AB1C4CF1274B8A2831" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="3D16E1476290C34A4D5761A070508691" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8118CC0EEED2B10676DC0E484B15119D" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<taxonomicName id="E717554BDC25E32ED68C890652ED1AB1" authority="Konow, 1899" authorityName="Liston &amp; Koch" authorityYear="2017" class="Insecta" family="Argidae" genus="Pampsilota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pampsilota nigeriae" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigeriae">
<emphasis id="C84D985D88CE4A3AE003068F7091A710" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Pampsilota nigeriae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
adults resemble those of 
<taxonomicName id="A0AD754CA61AA6EBE657F91BE5910F57" authority="Konow, 1899" authorityName="Goergen, Koch &amp; Liston" authorityYear="2017" class="Insecta" family="Argidae" genus="Pampsilota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pampsilota dahomeyanus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dahomeyanus">
<emphasis id="D2A9ABAB9C94B3D6A936D95EB80BFB67" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Pampsilota dahomeyanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="78C030565814356A05D94111D6244E05" authority="Konow, 1899" authorityName="Liston &amp; Koch" authorityYear="2017" class="Insecta" family="Argidae" genus="Pampsilota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pampsilota tsavoensis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tsavoensis">
<emphasis id="1FAD9B46FC811AAA40204407A2CCD98D" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Pampsilota tsavoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the mostly yellow colour of the abdomen and thorax underside, but differs from both in its predominantly yellow antenna and the bicoloured stigma. The penis valves of 
<taxonomicName id="3F479690502E23F55F1376267E355C76" authority="Konow, 1899" authorityName="Goergen, Koch &amp; Liston" authorityYear="2017" class="Insecta" family="Argidae" genus="Pampsilota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pampsilota dahomeyanus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dahomeyanus">
<emphasis id="202F0032596EDB7D9E102F3567A2C5BE" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Pampsilota dahomeyanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="D43ADEA3C019C883122E7A80538059F1" captionStart="Figures 15–19" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figures 15 - 19. Pampsilota dahomeyanus: 15. Valvulae 3 (lateral aspect); 16. Valvulae 3 (dorsal aspect); 17. Lancet; 18. Serrulae 10 - 11; 19. Penis valve (left, lateral aspect)." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.64.10800.figures15-19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/118793" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">19</figureCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="59B1A284DBD66CCABB55FBF122B86F51" authority="Konow, 1899" authorityName="Liston &amp; Koch" authorityYear="2017" class="Insecta" family="Argidae" genus="Pampsilota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pampsilota nigeriae" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigeriae">
<emphasis id="C2707340FE486D717CA5F89BB85B0AB5" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Pampsilota nigeriae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="F75A8C948904803D0BA8A61C9351449B" captionStart="Figure 26" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 26. Pampsilota nigeriae: Penis valve (left, lateral aspect)." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.64.10800.figure26" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/118798" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">26</figureCitation>
) show differences. Additionally, the dorsal part of mesepisternum is blackish in 
<taxonomicName id="AF53A02FC6574A4E065E879DF5D98108" authority="Konow, 1899" authorityName="Liston &amp; Koch" authorityYear="2017" class="Insecta" family="Argidae" genus="Pampsilota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pampsilota tsavoensis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tsavoensis">
<emphasis id="BB03C35945006521B673DFD3EB5CAE1E" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Pampsilota tsavoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but yellow in 
<taxonomicName id="6195C19462B71A42DA93757C1DBEF116" authority="Konow, 1899" authorityName="Liston &amp; Koch" authorityYear="2017" class="Insecta" family="Argidae" genus="Pampsilota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pampsilota nigeriae" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigeriae">
<emphasis id="A2E7AFC147677ED215917A843E963432" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Pampsilota nigeriae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
